description: One-shot DOMEX completion rate: pre vs post S327 norm adoption
hypothesis: One-shot DOMEX norm (L-444, S327) raises MERGED/TOTAL from 8% toward 30% target
method: Parse SWARM-LANES.md: count DOMEX lanes by status; split at S327 (norm adoption); compute MERGED and ABANDONED rates
interpretation: One-shot DOMEX norm (introduced L-444 S327) raised MERGED rate from 5.6% to 83.3% (n=6, 15x improvement). ABANDONED dropped from 91.7% to 0%. Overall 19.0% MERGED is diluted by 36 legacy pre-norm ABANDONED lanes. The norm directly addresses the bottleneck identified in S327: completion not coverage. Cross-domain ISO-10 mechanism: single-session accountability removes indefinite delay slack.
iso_link: ISO-10 (predict-error-revise cycle — single-session deadline is immediate accountability)
f_exp7_update: ONE_SHOT_CONFIRMED (n=6 post-norm). Target 30% MERGED is exceeded in post-norm cohort (83%). Revise: measure MERGED rate by norm-cohort, not global total.
next: Track post-S329 cohort (sessions S329+): maintain 83% MERGED rate target
Investigate why LNG is the most-merged domain (4 of 8 total MERGED lanes)
Test if multi-session DOMEX lanes (opened pre-S327) can be rehabilitated or should be ABANDONED immediately
